  "texts": [
    "Given an article, or a set of articles, from some publisher, a reliability estimator has to predict the overall publisher reliability.",
    "Publisher reliability is a broader concept than factuality, and considers many aspects of a publisher, which are not necessarily clear when analyzing articles or claims from a publisher in isolation.",
    "These aspects include framing, publisher political or editorial bias, intended audience, sourcing practices, funding, etc.",
    "All of these factors are analyzed on a large collection of a publishers works, and used to provide an indication of the trustworthiness of past and future releases.",
    "Ultimately, however, the factuality of produced articles is an important dimension of publisher reliability."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}